    <div class="policy-section" id="s1">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">01</div>
        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      </div>
      <p>SportTrack.ai Ltd ("<strong>SportTrack</strong>", "<strong>we</strong>", "<strong>us</strong>", or "<strong>our</strong>") is a company registered in England and Wales. We operate the platform and services available at <strong>sporttrack.ai</strong> and its subdomains.</p>
      <p>We act as the <strong>data controller</strong> for personal data processed in connection with our website, platform, and related services. This means we determine the purposes and means of processing your personal data.</p>
      <p>For all data protection enquiries, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@sporttrack.ai">privacy@sporttrack.ai</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s2">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">02</div>
        <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
      </div>
      <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, email address, and password when creating an account</li>
        <li>Organisation name, job title, and contact details</li>
        <li>Payment information (processed securely via third-party payment providers)</li>
        <li>Communications you send to us, including support requests</li>
        <li>Any other data you upload or enter into our platform</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address, browser type, and operating system</li>
        <li>Pages visited, time spent, and navigation paths</li>
        <li>Device identifiers and referral URLs</li>
        <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies (see Section 9)</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Information from Third Parties</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Data from social login providers (e.g. Google or LinkedIn) if you choose to sign in this way</li>
        <li>Information from analytics or advertising partners where applicable</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="highlight-box">
        We do not knowingly collect <strong>special category data</strong> (e.g. health data, biometric data, racial or ethnic origin) unless you explicitly provide it and we have a lawful basis to process it.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s3">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">03</div>
        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
      </div>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Service Delivery</strong></td><td>Creating and managing your account; providing platform features and AI-driven insights</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Communications</strong></td><td>Sending transactional emails, account alerts, and customer support responses</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Marketing</strong></td><td>Sending promotional content where you have opted in; you may opt out at any time</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Improvement &amp; Analytics</strong></td><td>Understanding how our platform is used to improve features and fix issues</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal &amp; Compliance</strong></td><td>Complying with legal obligations; fraud prevention; enforcing our terms of service</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Security</strong></td><td>Protecting our platform and users from unauthorised access or abuse</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s4">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">04</div>
        <h2>Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      </div>
      <p>Under the UK GDPR, we rely on the following legal bases to process your personal data:</p>
      <div class="pills-row">
        <span class="pill">📋 Contract</span>
        <span class="pill">⚖️ Legal Obligation</span>
        <span class="pill">✅ Consent</span>
        <span class="pill">🎯 Legitimate Interests</span>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing necessary to provide our services under a contract or in preparation to enter one.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Processing required to comply with applicable laws (e.g. financial record-keeping, responding to lawful authority requests).</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have given clear, specific consent (e.g. marketing communications or non-essential cookies). You may withdraw consent at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> Where we have a legitimate business interest that does not override your rights (e.g. fraud prevention, improving our services). We conduct a balancing test before relying on this basis.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s5">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">05</div>
        <h2>Sharing Your Data</h2>
      </div>
      <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share it with the following categories of third parties:</p>
      <h3>Service Providers &amp; Sub-processors</h3>
      <p>Trusted suppliers who process data on our behalf under contractual data protection obligations, including: cloud infrastructure providers, payment processors, email delivery services, and analytics tools.</p>
      <h3>Business Transfers</h3>
      <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of our business, your data may transfer to the successor entity. We will notify you in advance and your rights under this policy will be maintained.</p>
      <h3>Legal Disclosures</h3>
      <p>We may disclose your data where required by law, court order, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of SportTrack.ai, our users, or others.</p>
      <h3>With Your Consent</h3>
      <p>We may share your data with any other third party where you have given explicit consent.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s6">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">06</div>
        <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
      </div>
      <p>Some of our service providers are based outside the UK. Where we transfer personal data to countries without an equivalent level of data protection, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>UK adequacy regulations (countries recognised by the ICO as providing adequate protection)</li>
        <li>UK International Data Transfer Agreements (IDTAs) or addenda to EU Standard Contractual Clauses</li>
        <li>Other lawful transfer mechanisms approved by the ICO</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may request a copy of applicable transfer safeguards by contacting <a href="mailto:privacy@sporttrack.ai">privacy@sporttrack.ai</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s7">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">07</div>
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      </div>
      <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes described in this policy, or as required by law.</p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Retention Period</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Account &amp; profile data</td><td>Duration of account + 2 years after closure</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Financial / transaction records</td><td>7 years (UK tax law requirement)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Marketing consent records</td><td>Until consent withdrawn + 1 year</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Support correspondence</td><td>3 years from last interaction</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Log &amp; security data</td><td>Up to 12 months</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>After the retention period, we securely delete or anonymise your data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s8">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">08</div>
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      </div>
      <p>Under the UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018, you have the following rights:</p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Right</th><th>What It Means</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Access</strong></td><td>Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you (Subject Access Request)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Rectification</strong></td><td>Ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Erasure</strong></td><td>Request deletion of your data in certain circumstances ("right to be forgotten")</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Restriction</strong></td><td>Ask us to restrict processing of your data in certain circumstances</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Portability</strong></td><td>Receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Objection</strong></td><td>Object to processing based on legitimate interests or for direct marketing</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Withdraw Consent</strong></td><td>Withdraw any consent you have given at any time, without affecting prior processing</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="highlight-box">
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@sporttrack.ai"><strong>privacy@sporttrack.ai</strong></a>. We will respond within <strong>30 days</strong> as required by UK GDPR. There is no charge for most requests.
      </div>
      <p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong> at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank">ico.org.uk</a> or by calling 0303 123 1113.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s9">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">09</div>
        <h2>Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
      </div>
      <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to operate our platform and understand how it is used.</p>
      <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Required for the platform to function (e.g. authentication, session management). These cannot be disabled.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> Help us understand visitor behaviour to improve our service. Used only with your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing cookies:</strong> Used to show relevant advertising and measure campaign effectiveness. Used only with your consent.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can manage cookie preferences via our Cookie Preference Centre (accessible from our website footer) or by adjusting your browser settings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s10">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">10</div>
        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      </div>
      <p>Our services are not directed at children under the age of <strong>13</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13 without verifiable parental consent.</p>
      <p>If you believe we have inadvertently collected data from a child under 13, please contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:privacy@sporttrack.ai">privacy@sporttrack.ai</a> and we will delete such data promptly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section" id="s11">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="section-num">11</div>
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      </div>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make material changes, we will:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Update the "Effective Date" at the top of this page</li>
        <li>Notify registered users by email where required</li>
        <li>Display a prominent notice on our platform</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Continued use of our services after any changes take effect constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
    </div>

